column5: Leaving for gullrock in 2 weeks. How is the fishing and the weather? Any Patterns or places the walleyes might be at? Also seems not as much activity as in the past on this walleye/canada board?

We were at a GUll Rock camp the week of 7-19 and was amazed at how empty the camp was. There was only one other cabin occupied, and one camper that left mid week. In 20 plus years going to Gull Rock I have never seen such low numbers of people. Even on the lake it seemed for a few days we had the place to ourselves. Fishing was great as always, lots of numbers and a lot of overs.

Interesting, we stayed at five lakes lodge the first week in August and the camp was full. All the popular spots we fished were busy and at times we would simply move to avoid the boats. Seemed prety much business as usual. I had actually expected we would see lower traffic but not so that week.
I'm not familair with this camp. where is it?
You can see it from the highway, immediately on your right, as you cross Bug river heading North. Been staying there for years.
I'm familiar with five lakes, never heard it called Gull Rock camp. Thanks
Sorry I thought you were asking me.....I think the other poster said a Gullrock camp and actually did not name the camp.
